abstract: Leaked South African intelligence service documents include 2012 report by Israeli intelligence agency Mossad saying that Iran did not appear close to second stage of nuclear weapon production; report contradicts Prime Min Benjamin Netanyahu, who had only three weeks earlier given dire speech at United Nations warning that Iran was only few months away from making nuclear bomb.
lead_paragraph: Prime Minister Benjamin Netanyahu’s dire warning in 2012 about Iran’s nuclear program differed sharply from an analysis just weeks later by Israel’s foreign intelligence agency, a leaked report showed.

headline.main: Israeli Views on Iran Diverged, Reports Say
